First preprocess data. (call in R...)
```{r}
library(rmarkdown)
render("0-preprocess.Rmd")
```

Calculate GGMs:
```{bash}
Rscript R/apply-ggm_batch.R
```

Perform validation
```{bash}
Rscript R/validate-ggm_batch.R 
```

summarize validation results into one table:
```{bash}
# ignore failed runs...
grep "Execution halted" *.validation.out | cut -f 1 -d "." | uniq > results/failed.txt
while read p ; do rm results/$p.validation.txt ; done < results/failed.txt

cat results/*.validation.txt | sort | uniq | sort -r > results/validation.summary.txt

```

Display the validation results in a neat RMarkdown document
```{r}
library(rmarkdown)
render("3-render-validation.Rmd")
```
